England Declares on 496-5 in First Test With Sri Lanka, Leading by 96 Runs

-- B y   C h r i s   E l s e r
-- 
2011-05-30T14:43:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/england-declares-on-496-5-in-first-test-with-sri-lanka-leading-by-96-runs.html
England  declared on 496-5, forcing
Sri Lanka to bat on the final day of their rain-shortened first
cricket Test in Cardiff.  The visitors were trailing by 96 runs at the start of their
second innings after finishing 400 all out to start the match.  England bowler Chris Tremlett took the wicket of Tharanga
Paranavitana, caught by Andrew Strauss, in the second over this
afternoon, and then caught and bowled Tillakaratne Dilshan in
the fourth over. Sri Lanka was reduced to 10-2 in its second
innings.  Jonathan Trott  reached 203, supported by Alastair’s 133 and
Ian Bell’s unbeaten 103. Eoin Morgan was on 14 when England
declared.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  